    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Federal Disaster Assistance Nonprofit Fairness Act of 2013 - Amends the Robert T. Stafford Disaster Relief and Emergency Assistance Act to include community centers, including tax-exempt houses of worship, as &quot;private nonprofit facilities&quot; for purposes of disaster relief and emergency assistance eligibility under such Act.</p> <p>Makes a church, synagogue, mosque, temple, or other house of worship, and a private nonprofit facility operated by a religious organization, eligible for federal contributions for the repair, restoration, and replacement of facilities damaged or destroyed by a major disaster, without regard to the religious character of the facility or the primary religious use of the facility.</p> <p>Makes this Act applicable to the provision of assistance in response to a major disaster or emergency declared on or after October 28, 2012.</p>]]></text>
